## JavaScript
JavaScript is a high-level programming language.

## Data types
In programming, data types are important. 
Knowing which data type is stored in a variable, enables us to perform specific computational operations.

## Data types
    *String
    *Integer and float
    *Boolean
    *Null
    *Undefined

### Data type examples
var number1 = 16      //Integer
var number2 = 12.2    //Float
var lastName = "Johnson";          //String
var empty;              //undefined
var empty2 = null;      //Null
var container1 = 2+3+"Johnson"     //String      //Outputs 5Johnson
var container2 = 2+"Johnson"+3    //String    //Outputs 2Johnson3
var boolean1 = true;    //Boolean
var boolean2 = false;   //Boolean

## Checking data types
Using the typeof operator you can request the data type of a variable.

Type                    Result
var x = "al";
alert (typeof x);       “string”
var x = 121;
alert (typeof x);       “number”
var x = true;
alert (typeof x);       “boolean”
alert (typeof x);       “undefined”